## 1. GLOBAL RESOURCE CAPACITY ANALYSIS

### 1.1 Caloric Efficiency (Food)
* **Current State (FAO 2023/2024):** Global food production is currently sufficient to feed approximately 10.2 billion people.
* **The Mammon Friction:** Approximately 31% of all food produced (approx. 1.3 billion tons) is lost or wasted due to market-driven logistical inefficiencies, aesthetic retail standards, and speculative hoarding (Source: FAO Food Loss Index).
* **Flow Optimization:** By shifting to *Local Capacity Sufficiency* and eliminating market-driven standards, we recover a latent capacity of **+30%**.
* **Result:** $1.25$ (current surplus) $\times 1.30$ (waste recovery) = **1.62x Total Capacity.**

### 1.2 Energy Entropy (Power)
* **Current State (IEA World Energy Outlook 2023):** Total renewable potential (Solar/Wind) exceeds total human demand by a factor of >100x.
* **The Mammon Friction:** Capital expenditure (CapEx) hurdles and fossil fuel subsidies ($7 trillion in 2022, IMF) artificially restrict the transition to a zero-marginal-cost energy grid.
* **Flow Optimization:** Redirecting Mammon-era subsidies to decentralized Flow-nodes (Micro-grids) reduces transmission loss and eliminates price-driven energy poverty.

